  "description": [
    {
      "type": "heading2",
      "content": {
        "text": "What you’ll do",
        "spans": []
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": {
        "text": "Come along and learn how to create quality video journalism content. You can come individually or as a group of friends – for the session you’ll be working in pairs and we’ll provide iPads for you to use while you’re here. The workshop will show you how to use day-to-day technology like your own mobile phone or tablet to communicate your ideas about issues that matter to you.",
        "spans": []
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "heading2",
      "content": {
        "text": "About your facilitators",
        "spans": []
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": {
        "text": "Abdul Boudiaf will teach you all the videography skills you’ll need for the session. ",
        "spans": []
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "heading2",
      "content": {
        "text": "Where we’ll be",
        "spans": []
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": {
        "text": "The workshops will take place in our Studio on level 1. When you enter the museum, head up the stairs or take the lift to floor 1 and follow the signs. Each workshop has 25 spaces available. Sign-up will open at 13.30 in the Studio. Places are given out on a first-come, first-served basis.",
        "spans": []
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": {
        "text": "These workshops are for anyone aged 14–19. If you’re visiting the museum with parents, they are welcome to drop you off at our Studio.\n\n",
        "spans": []
      }
    }
  ],
